<h3 dir="ltr">Customizable Settings</h3>
<p dir="ltr">Copy trading platforms, like ATFX, allow all Followers to customise certain settings to attain optimal risk management on their accounts. This is because account sizes differ. A trader with a $1,000 account who follows a Provider with a $100,000 account cannot take the same lot sizes as the Provider, as this would not be a good risk management practice. This is why copy trading platforms allow Followers to adjust risk settings, take profit/stop loss settings and other metrics that are defined uniquely to each platform.</p>
<p dir="ltr">Looking at the ATFX CopyTrade interface, we can see a few metrics that Followers can adjust. For instance, how is the trade size adjusted?</p>
<p dir="ltr">There is a tool known as the Volume Scaling tool. This is used to set the ratio of the copied trade&#8217;s volume to that of the Provider. Three settings are recognized: Autoscale, Multiply and Fixed. A volume multiplier allows you to specify the fraction of the Follower&#8217;s trade size in relation to that of the Provider. If a Follower wants his lot size to be a tenth of the Provider&#8217;s lot size, the volume scaling is set to Multiply, and the Volume Multiplier is set to 0.1.</p>
<p dir="ltr"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-46231 aligncenter" src="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Multiplier-volume.jpg" alt="Multiplier-volume" width="519" height="451" srcset="https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Multiplier-volume.jpg 519w, https://www.atfx.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Multiplier-volume-300x261.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 519px) 100vw, 519px" /></p>
